{"questionId":"12595","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The width of a rectangular garden is 4.5 metres shorter than its length, which is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> metres.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The perimeter of the garden is 111 m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an equation for the perimeter of the garden in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2x + 2\\left( {x - 4.5} \\right) = 111\"> <mn>2</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4.5</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>111</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong> (C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from their expression for the width from part (a).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12595","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down an equation for the perimeter of the garden in terms of x .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Prior learning"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}